0th anniversary, the book covers the system's origins, political landscape, varied missions, the different types of institutions, international partnerships, leadership, future directions, and more. Other state systems have been studied more closely and in depth (California, Michigan, Texas), and this book is a long overdue effort to bring New York into that conversation. Edited by a past interim chancellor of the system, and two SUNY history professors, and with a foreword by current chancellor Nancy L. Zimpher, this book is essential for anyone who has a stake in public higher education in New York state, or indeed, public higher education anywhere.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aHigher education and statezNew York (State)xHistory. 4aEducation : Education. 4aEducation : History of Education. 4aHistory : History. 4aNew York/Regional : New York/Regional. 7aEDUCATION / Higher.2bisacsh1 aClark, John B., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLeslie, W. Bruce, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aO'Brien, Kenneth P., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aZimpher, Chancellor Nancy L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZimpher, Nancy L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143843304240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438433042423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438433042/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles